str2: From a derivative of tugchano; fortuitous, i.e. Fortunate; Tychicus, a Christian.
A primary particle; but, and, etc.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: From apo and stello; set apart, i.e. to send out literally or figuratively.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
Ephesus, a coast city, capital of the Roman province Asia. Probably of foreign origin; Ephesus, a city of Asia Minor.
